## 2. Architecture Assessment

```mermaid
graph TD
    A["Raw CSVs/TSVs"] -->|ETL Pipeline 01-07| B["MySQL 8.0<br>biblio_db"]
    B -->|SQL Views 08| C["Pre-computed Aggregates"]
    C --> D["Flask Backend<br>(Connection Pool)"]
    D -->|REST JSON| E["Frontend<br>HTML/Jinja2 + D3.js"]
    D --> F["Flask-Caching<br>(SimpleCache)"]
```

**Strengths:**
- Single-table [papers](file:///c:/Users/public.LAPTOP-17PSCTIQ/Desktop/MATHIMATA/proxorimena/project/backend/routes/years.py#20-40) design with `type` discriminator is pragmatic and well-documented
- SQL Views push computation into the DBMS layer (as the prof explicitly requires)
- Connection pooling with `mysql-connector-python`
- Clean Blueprint-based route separation

**Weaknesses:**
- `SimpleCache` is process-local and resets on restart. For a demo app this is fine, but if you want to impress: mention Redis as a future improvement in your report
- No logging framework (just `print()` and `console.error()`)
- No environment variable management (`.env` file)

