## 3. Backend Deep Dive

### 3.1 Bugs & Issues

| File | Issue | Severity |
|---|---|---|
| [app.py](file:///c:/Users/public.LAPTOP-17PSCTIQ/Desktop/MATHIMATA/proxorimena/project/backend/app.py#L76-L82) | [add_header](file:///c:/Users/public.LAPTOP-17PSCTIQ/Desktop/MATHIMATA/proxorimena/project/backend/app.py#76-83) contradicts itself: sets `Cache-Control: no-cache, no-store, must-revalidate` then immediately overwrites with `Cache-Control: public, max-age=0`. The second line wins — effectively disabling the first. **Pick one strategy.** | 🔴 High |
| [journals.py](file:///c:/Users/public.LAPTOP-17PSCTIQ/Desktop/MATHIMATA/proxorimena/project/backend/routes/journals.py#L76-L116) | [get_papers()](file:///c:/Users/public.LAPTOP-17PSCTIQ/Desktop/MATHIMATA/proxorimena/project/backend/routes/years.py#20-40) for journals has **no `except` block** — unlike every other route. If the query fails, Flask will return a raw 500 traceback to the client. | 🔴 High |
| [journals.py](file:///c:/Users/public.LAPTOP-17PSCTIQ/Desktop/MATHIMATA/proxorimena/project/backend/routes/journals.py#L121) | [search_journals()](file:///c:/Users/public.LAPTOP-17PSCTIQ/Desktop/MATHIMATA/proxorimena/project/backend/routes/journals.py#118-137) doesn't strip or sanitize the query `q`. Conference search does `strip()` + regex cleanup — journals do not. This inconsistency could cause MySQL FT-search errors with special characters. | 🟡 Medium |
| [years.py](file:///c:/Users/public.LAPTOP-17PSCTIQ/Desktop/MATHIMATA/proxorimena/project/backend/routes/years.py#L20-L40) | [get_papers()](file:///c:/Users/public.LAPTOP-17PSCTIQ/Desktop/MATHIMATA/proxorimena/project/backend/routes/years.py#20-40) for years uses `LIMIT %s` with a query param `limit` but **no pagination**. Hardcoded to `default=100` but the frontend requests `limit=250`. With 200K+ papers per year, this is an incomplete implementation. | 🟡 Medium |
| [db.py](file:///c:/Users/public.LAPTOP-17PSCTIQ/Desktop/MATHIMATA/proxorimena/project/backend/db.py#L42-L61) | [execute_query()](file:///c:/Users/public.LAPTOP-17PSCTIQ/Desktop/MATHIMATA/proxorimena/project/backend/db.py#42-61) has a dual path (conn=None → context manager, conn not None → manual cursor). This legacy code path is confusing and could leak connections if an exception occurs between [get_db_connection()](file:///c:/Users/public.LAPTOP-17PSCTIQ/Desktop/MATHIMATA/proxorimena/project/backend/db.py#23-28) and `try`. It was supposed to be removed per the earlier refactor PR. | 🟡 Medium |

